        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 7. Porcellidium viride (Philippi, 1840). Male: (A) detail of antennule coupling denticles; (B, C) P5 (ventral); (D) maxilla; (F, G) antennule (* peg or ventral process). Female: (E) showing extent of colour pattern of specimens from Loch HYne, Ireland. Scale bar: A = 0.06 mm. B, D, F, G = 0.08 mm." ;
